description.2: With his privacy at risk, Spidey races against the clock to stop a surveillance mission by the Tinkerer and the Beetle that threatens to expose all super hero identities!
description.5: Refugees of the this dark future head into the past (our present) to escape the Abomination, who has taken the despotic place that the Maestro has left. But have they escaped one Abomination only to find themselves at the mercy of the Abomination of the present?
description.6: Ben Reilly is just another pawn in Green Goblin’s plot against Peter Parker! In this epic tale, “The Night of the Goblin,” Norman Osborn makes his final play in a plan that took years to hatch.
description.8: The first appearance of Blind Al!  Deadpool takes on a mission to Antarctica, where he finds himself face-to-face with Sasquatch (Walter Langkowski) of Alpha Flight!! After swindling some Girl Scouts, Deadpool takes on another "easy" mission -- taking out an unmanned research station. Simple, right? Unfortunately, it's not only very manned...but also brimming with gamma radiation!
description.10: Witness the introduction of the Thunderbolts, America's new premier superhero team! Can the Hulk withstand their assault? And why are they attacking the Jade Giant in the first place?
description.14: When Iceman's cover as a member of Graydon Creed's group is blown it will cost him dearly...
description.22: When the royal court of Eiattu 6 came to Rogue Squadron to collect their princess-Plourr Ilo, who was unaware of her heritage-they did so to help put an end to their planet's internal rebellion. They reasoned that a strong figurehead might pull the people together-what they couldn't know was that a strong-willed princess might have her own view of how things should be run.
description.24: When Gav and Jori Daragon set off to map the uncharted regions of hyperspace, they knew they were risking their lives. But they thought it would be an unsuspected cluster of debris that would take them out of the game, not their successful discovery of a series of hyperspace "short cuts." The Sith Empire wants to know where these routes are - wants to hold the only map to these routes - so that it can maintain an iron grip on the galaxy. And the lives of a couple of explorers mean very little to these masters of the dark side of the Force.
description.27: Magneto and his Astonishing X-Men finally have the opportunity they've been waiting for. It's time to take out Apocalypse! Plus, Magneto versus Diablo and Crusher Creel, the Absorbing Man!
description.30: As the Chameleon is being treated by Dr. Kafka, Peter and Mary Jane Parker mourn the loss of their first-born child.
description.32: Featuring the Master of Illusion, Mysterio! While on a trip in Arizona, Peter discovers that weird events reported by locals stem from a sinister Spidey foe…
description.35: In a dark future, the rule of Maestro is at an end. How will humanity begin to rebuild and what role does the Abomination play in this new world?
description.42: The finale to Ben's latest duel with his darker half, Kaine! Can he come out on top in this epic clash of clones - and still save his friend Janine?
description.43: Gaunt ambushes Peter and Ben, and he's out for blood! But what is he attacking them for? And why does Mary Jane have to go into labor NOW?
description.44: Two titanic team-ups for the price of one! First, Spidey and X-Man Gambit go club hopping in New York City's Greenwich Village — and Tombstone's on the guest list! Then, the Web-Head and the Web-Foot join forces as Spidey and Howard the Duck run a fowl of the Circus of Crime!
description.45: Elektra vs. Bullseye — Round Two! It's the rematch of the century as the beautiful assassin comes face-to-face with her nemesis, the cold-blooded killer known as Bullseye! He murdered her once; can he do it again?! This match ends in someone's sudden death!
description.49: GAUNT is stronger than ever, and he's got Peter and Ben in his sights! But even if the pair of Spideys make it out alive, will they be able to handle the horrible tragedy that has befallen the Parker family?
description.55: It's a new beginning for the Hulk! But new beginnings aren't always what old friends want, and Hulk finds himself at odds with his old teammates of the Pantheon!
description.56: This is it! The epic conclusion to the Clone Saga and the story of Ben Reilly!
description.57: Mary Jane Watson, before she's had her first date with Peter Parker, has her first Spider-Man encounter!
description.59: The X-Men must stop Havok and his Brotherhood from killing J. Jonah Jameson!
description.65: From the pages of GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY! A brand new series from SAM HUMPHRIES and PACO MEDINA! In this exciting first issue, Peter Quill battles the Badoon, fights to save an orphanage, and still finds time for some flirting with Kitty Pryde--but it's all in a day's work for the STAR-LORD!
description.66: A jam-packed special outlining the former, current, and future class of X-Men! In a yearbook format, Xavier’s Institute is outlined by its students and their favorite extracurricular activities. A must-read for any X-fan!
description.67: The squadron's roster has contained Corellian heroes and Alderaanian fighter aces, but when the royal court of Eiattu 6 comes to reclaim their princess from the ranks of Rogue Squadron, it's a surprise to everyone... especially the princess!
description.68: Marka Ragnos ruled the galaxy with an iron fist. He was the Dark Lord of the Sith - the most powerful of the most powerful. But now he is dead. And two innocent hyperspace explorers, Gav and Jori Daragon, may follow suit if they get caught between the warring factions hoping to fill the Dark Lord void.
description.73: The secret identities of Gaunt AND his mysterious employer are revealed! Could this crack open the case of who's behind the Clone Saga?!
description.78: Leading the charge, Nightcrawler and Excalibur retaliate against Black Air for Douglock's abduction.
description.79: The Hulk has emerged stronger than ever on the other side of his latest crisis - but with no memories! With Hulk not even recognizing those closest to him like Betty Ross, can anyone hope to subdue the rage within the Jade Giant?
description.80: Spidey and Daredevil team up once again to come down on the mysterious Don Fortunato and his high-powered Hydra weaponry threatening New York City!
description.91: Spider-Man attempts to rescue the kidnapped MJ from Kingpin's clutches, but the crime lord seems unshakeable. Thankfully, Peter discovers Kingpin's singular vulnerability… his wife, Vanessa.
description.95: Spider-Man - fugitive! Knowing his friend Janine is innocent, Ben breaks her out of police custody which puts them both on the lam! But they won't get far before Kaine makes his next move!
description.96: What's worse: fighting a swarm of mutant bees or being late for a hot date? Ask Ben Reilly, currently in both predicaments!
description.98: Daredevil broke her heart, Bullseye killed her, and the Hand orchestrated her resurrection — now the beautiful assassin is taking control of her life in her own ongoing title! This landmark issue establishes Elektra's new life, introduces a new cast of characters, and brings back a very old yearning to kill!

0.text: The god-like Scrier makes their first appearance! This vastly powerful being has leveled a deal with the Silver Surfer, one that will challenge the Power Cosmic to its core!

1.text: At stake! The life of Bruce Banner’s son, David! If that is David’s true identity...

3.text: Will our merry mutants become media darlings in the maddening Mojoverse?

4.text: Smash through the legend of the Hulk with Bruce Banner’s defining origin. How was this monster-man created? And what were Banner’s earliest days like as the Green Goliath?

5.text: Refugees of this dark future head into the past (our present) to escape the Abomination, who has taken the despotic place that the Maestro has left. But have they escaped one Abomination only to find themselves at the mercy of the Abomination of the present?

7.text: Matt and Karen find out whom Rosalind really is! Daredevil takes on the Absorbing Man!

8.text: After swindling some Girl Scouts, Deadpool takes on another "easy" mission -- taking out an unmanned research station. Simple, right? Unfortunately, it's not only very manned...but also brimming with gamma radiation!

After swindling some Girl Scouts, Deadpool takes on another "easy" mission -- taking out an unmanned research station. Simple, right? Unfortunately, it's not only very manned...but also brimming with gamma radiation!

9.text: Kitty Pryde must reconcile with Douglock’s true identity.

12.text: Graydon Creed’s violent rhetoric leads to his assassination!

13.text: To stop Giganto's rampage in New York City, The Fantastic Four joins forces with The Avengers!

15.text: Not all is as it seems as Logan's time in Japan reaches its epic conclusion!

16.text: Storm is caught up in a whirlwind from her past as a thief...the eternal Candra comes calling!

18.text: New Atlantis may unearth several memories for Silver Surfer, however its ruler is now dead. What is Atlantis without Namor? And can the Surfer recover his full, former self?

20.text: Banshee reflects on his relationship with his daughter, Theresa, around Thanksgiving. Chamber feels challenged by his relationship with Paige.

23.text: He is Spider-Man’s sworn nemesis, the bringer of so much evil and chaos that he has, on several occasions, nearly destroyed Peter Parker. Now, get in on the ground floor of the Green Goblin with this readers’ guide on his greatest and most pivotal stories!

25.text: After brawling with the World Party mercenaries, Steve rushes home to ensure his wife and son's safety. But when he finds Nick Fury of S.H.I.E.L.D. waiting for him in his home, a fate worse than death for his family is revealed.

27.text: Magneto and his Astonishing X-Men finally have the opportunity they've been waiting for. It's time to take out Apocalypse! Plus, Magneto versus Diablo and Crusher Creel, the Absorbing Man!

28.text: The Merc with a Mouth faces off against the clones of Marvel's most distinguished deceased.

29.text: The Fantastic Four face off against two of their greatest enemies: Mole Man and Namor, The Sub-Mariner!

30.text: As the Chameleon is being treated by Dr. Kafka, Peter and Mary Jane Parker mourn the loss of their first-born child.

31.text: A black and white one-shot unlike any other! Michael Golden enters the inner sanctum of Doctor Strange! And, Jose Ladronn opens the tomb of Dracula! (Note: this only contains the Into the Tomb! and Strange Reflections stories)

33.text: Cyclops, Jean Grey and Storm join the action as the X-Men are vexed by the Vanisher — as well as by Sentinels, Spiral and the Hellfire Club!

34.text: Learn all about the hotheaded herald of Galactus with Firelord’s definitive origin!

35.text: In a dark future, the rule of Maestro is at an end. How will humanity begin to rebuild and what role does the Abomination play in this new world?

36.text: In an effort to save his own life, Tony Stark dons the experimental Prometheum Armor. But "Iron Man" isn't out of the woods yet, as a giant green monster calling himself The Hulk is hell-bent on crushing Stark's skull.

37.text: The Shatterstar Saga continues! Cable and Shatterstar are stranded in a virtual reality re-creating Mojoworld…100 years in the future!

38.text: The Silver Surfer guest-stars! Cyclops and his team are caught in a cosmic calamity that leaves them fugitives...in space!

39.text: Selene sets her plans in motions and reforms the Hellfire Club!

41.text: En Sabah Nur and Nephri are sold out by Logos! Will Nephri still care for the future Apocalypse when his face is revealed to the public? And Will En Sabah Nur take Rama-Tut's offer to be his heir?

42.text: The finale to Ben's latest duel with his darker half, Kaine! Can he come out on top in this epic clash of clones - and still save his friend Janine?

44.text: Two titanic team-ups for the price of one! First, Spidey and X-Man Gambit go club hopping in New York City's Greenwich Village — and Tombstone's on the guest list! Then, the Web-Head and the Web-Foot join forces as Spidey and Howard the Duck run a fowl of the Circus of Crime!

45.text: Elektra vs. Bullseye — Round Two! It's the rematch of the century as the beautiful assassin comes face-to-face with her nemesis, the cold-blooded killer known as Bullseye! He murdered her once; can he do it again?! This match ends in someone's sudden death!

47.text: Artie, Leech, and Franklin Richards try to enjoy a night of trick-or-treating in Vermont. Nightmare confronts Emma Frost directly.

50.text: Into the Microverse! Following last issue’s kidnapping, Domino, Cable and Kane, confront Pyscho-Man on his home turf…and collect a few soldiers along the way!

51.text: Every Marvel fan's favorite publication! The Daily Bugle gets its very own spotlight!

52.text: Dirt Nap tries to absorb Venom and a battle ensues. But some unlikely allies show up that will give Venom a hand!

53.text: Karen debates Daredevil’s place in the world on her radio show!

54.text: Who is Douglock? And how much of this techno-organic being is the human that once was?

56.text: This is it! The epic conclusion to the Clone Saga and the story of Ben Reilly!

60.text: While imprisoned in Japan, Logan is attacked, while old enemies become new allies!

61.text: Bishop and Beast face the Herculean strength of a Greek demi-god!

62.text: Robbed of his emotions, Surfer returns to a post-Onslaught Earth in the hopes that Alicia Masters can reawaken his feelings. But when confronted with death, the Surfer remains unmoved. Plus, a mysterious being is trailing his every move…

63.text: Attempting to return to the Marvel Universe, the Black Knight Dane Whitman and Sersi are mistakenly transported to the 12th century where the Black Knight Eobar Garrington and his friend Bennet du Paris are crusaders!

65.text: Starlord has been missing for 22 years. When a rookie lawman in a corrupt judicial system finds a crashed sentient starship, he stumbles into a web of intrigue beyond his experience— as he is forced to become the new Starlord!

66.text: A jam-packed special outlining the former, current, and future class of X-Men! In a yearbook format, Xavier’s Institute is outlined by its students and their favorite extracurricular activities. A must-read for any X-fan!

71.text: Steve Rogers is plagued by terrible nightmares. In his dreams he sees the old war hero Captain America battling Nazis. Who really is Captain America and what does Steve Rogers have to do with him?

72.text: J. Jonah Jameson may be walking into a carefully crafted mob set-up…but not if Spider-Man can help it!

73.text: The secret identities of Gaunt AND his mysterious employer are revealed! Could this crack open the case of who's behind the Clone Saga?!

74.text: Warren Worthington III: X-Man, hero, and philanthropist. But after having his mind altered by Apocalypse, Angel became Archangel, shadow of death.  Witness the fallen Angel struggle with his descent into darkness, as he tries to maintain what’s left of his humanity.

76.text: It’s ClanDestine versus the X-Men in an extra-dimensional battle for the ages!

77.text: Daredevil stops Mysterio’s scam in its tracks!

80.text: Spidey and Daredevil team up once again to come down on the mysterious Don Fortunato and his high-powered Hydra weaponry threatening New York City!

82.text: Reed Richards, accompanied by his loyal friend Ben Grimm, heads out into the great scientific unknown aboard the spacecraft Excelsior! But something terrible is about to happen-something that Reed could not have accounted for...

84.text: Logan visits Japan to see an old friend, but another person from his past is targeting Logan for revenge!

85.text: Gambit and Magneto come to blows over a mix-up concerning Rogue!

87.text: When Hydra attacks the Stark International Buffalo Plant, a massive gamma explosion changes the lives of both Tony Stark and Bruce Banner.

88.text: Doctor Strange guest-stars! On Mojoworld, Gog and Ma'gog hold Cable and Shatterstar captive in order to wipe their brains for Mojo’s next televised special!

89.text: Nate and Threnody take in all the sites that New York City can offer. In another corner of the city, Selene approaches Sebastian Shaw with an offer too tempting to be cast aside.

92.text: Gambit finds himself in the middle of a war between the Thieves Guild and the Assassins — but what will become of the ragin’ Cajun’s brother?

93.text: Original X-Man Archangel flies into Uncanny Origins! Warren Worthington III went from a life of privilege and silver spoons, to gaining extraordinary abilities as the high-flying Angel! Plus, recount his darkest days as a Horseman of Apocalypse!

94.text: After the death of his father Baal, En Sabah Nur - the young man that will grow into Apocalypse - is on a mission to destroy the man responsible...Ozymandias, Egyptian warlord! But what are En Sabah Nur's true plans regarding him?

95.text: Spider-Man - fugitive! Knowing his friend Janine is innocent, Ben breaks her out of police custody which puts them both on the lam! But they won't get far before Kaine makes his next move!

97.text: The Great Game reaches its final round — but it stops being a game when one of Spidey's allies dies! Nightwatch, Rocket Racer, Cardiac, Prowler — who has fought his last fight?

98.text: Daredevil broke her heart, Bullseye killed her, and the Hand orchestrated her resurrection — now the beautiful assassin is taking control of her life in her own ongoing title! This landmark issue establishes Elektra's new life, introduces a new cast of characters, and brings back a very old yearning to kill!
